elements.2211.03016_3327b67e9b61d7102615bee71b21d: The SABRE (Sodium iodide with Active Background REjection) experiment aims to detect an annual rate modulation from dark matter interactions in ultra-high purity NaI(Tl) crystals in order to provide a model independent test of the signal observed by DAMA/LIBRA
elements.2211.03016_c330e29978a170007848c41124ca9: It is made up of two separate detectors; SABRE South located at the Stawell Underground Physics Laboratory (SUPL), in regional Victoria, Australia, and SABRE North at the Laboratori Nazionali del Gran Sasso (LNGS)
elements.2211.03016_56bee53650687ef96b1b3e6a11ed5: SABRE South is designed to disentangle seasonal or site-related effects from the dark matter-like modulated signal by using an active veto and muon detection system
elements.2211.03016_b8ebe954c6012d149d5821ed10206: Ultra-high purity NaI(Tl) crystals are immersed in a linear alkyl benzene (LAB) based liquid scintillator veto, further surrounded by passive steel and polyethylene shielding and a plastic scintillator muon veto
elements.2211.03016_ead6593e606c8f11a13306c3eda3d: Significant work has been undertaken to understand and mitigate the background processes, that take into account radiation from the detector materials, from both intrinsic and cosmogenic activated processes, and to understand the performance of both the crystal and veto systems

elements.2211.03016_fca8d1f9fcb3165f3c1b91cd3d65b: 2900 m water equivalent) within the Stawell Gold Mine and its construction has been completed in mid-2022
elements.2211.03016_15aae8ea141667505613efb610bda: The laboratory will house rare event physics searches, including the upcoming SABRE dark matter experiment, as well as measurement facilities to support low background physics experiments and applications such as radiobiology and quantum computing

elements.2211.03016_b9534ec8703f28205fd073848f019: This paper describes the setup and projections for the experiment, and the description of the underground laboratory.
elements.2211.03016_c3f0db365e7a8968bcfc86e41790e: Dark Matter (DM) represents one of the most important open problems in modern physics
elements.2211.03016_42c2e6984ac2381d2cda054f691fc: One search technique is direct detection which attempts to observe the recoil of a target after scattering with a DM particle, hypothesised as a WIMP (Weakly Interacting Massive Particles) with masses on the Gev/c
elements.2211.03016_6178250dd8157ed5daa82412cc08f: and cross sections on the weak scale
elements.2211.03016_b8f96fc7f248f9f1165977c1a91d4: This interaction rate should modulate annually, with a sinusoidal trend, due to the rotation of the Earth around the Sun as it moves through the galactic dark matter halo
elements.2211.03016_5bc3b7c0d6e66503fc4c2b0b29dae: To date, only one direct detection experiment, DAMA/LIBRA, has observed a modulation compatible with that expected from DM
elements.2211.03016_490baa36c71ff5a9a0bf8becce23e: However, this signal is in tension with every other direct detection experiment; all of which report null results for a standard WIMP
elements.2211.03016_68c71902c846acd1481e7ea6964fa: These are possible explanations: the majority of experiments do not use the same target material as DAMA/LIBRA and the current experiments with sodium iodide crystals do not achieve the same sensitivity
elements.2211.03016_2fde186e630527bdb84b42e2630cd: Further, it can be argued that the modulation observed by DAMA/LIBRA is due to seasonal effects, for example muons which also present a modulation with a maximum and minimum in the same period, in the Northern Hemisphere, as DM
elements.2211.03016_fbca2c10bf076739be2e7d3b547c1: The SABRE Collaboration was formed to provide a model independent test of this DAMA/LIBRA signal
elements.2211.03016_18cd4bf5064e1c106e0d1db5bf82b: It foresees two detectors located in two different hemispheres: SABRE North at Gran Sasso National Laboratory (LNGS), in Italy, and SABRE South at the Stawell Underground Physics Laboratory (SUPL), in Australia
elements.2211.03016_5235390425d8bff73176bca751d00: The two detectors have a number of common features as they are centred around the same detector module concept, and use common simulation, DAQ, and software frameworks
elements.2211.03016_80eb36a2cffadf8d0f562ba57008a: The two detectors differ in their shielding designs - where SABRE South will utilise a liquid scintillator system for in-situ evaluation and validation of the background to provide background rejection and particle identification
elements.2211.03016_d1441ba3e71bd44be1dbb1157d958: SABRE North has opted for a fully passive shielding since the organic scintillator has been phased out by LNGS
elements.2211.03016_0d2929c3f1134c00dba7832f0249f: The ultra-low background components will achieve the same sensitivity as DAMA/LIBRA; moreover, the site in the Southern Hemisphere will allow for the exclusion of systematic seasonal effects.
